INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '378f1740-fcd5-4e4b-9c75-ab0f6e9aaf2c',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Kubernetes Storage — PVs, StorageClasses, and StatefulSets Done Right$escape$,
  $escape$PersistentVolumes (PVs) decouple storage lifecycle from Pod lifecycle. You rarely create PVs manually — instead, a StorageClass drives dynamic provisioning: when a PersistentVolumeClaim (PVC) is created, the provisioner (e.g. `ebs.csi.aws.com`) spins up the backing volume automatically and binds it.

StatefulSets take this further by templating PVCs per replica via `volumeClaimTemplates`. Each Pod gets its own stable PVC — `data-postgres-0`, `data-postgres-1` — that survives Pod restarts and rescheduling. The PVC is NOT deleted when you scale down; you must clean it up manually.

Key decisions:
- `accessModes`: `ReadWriteOnce` for most block storage, `ReadWriteMany` only if your CSI driver supports it (e.g. EFS, NFS).
- `reclaimPolicy: Retain` on your StorageClass for production — prevents accidental data loss on PVC delete.
- `volumeBindingMode: WaitForFirstConsumer` delays provisioning until a Pod is scheduled, ensuring the volume lands in the correct AZ.

Mismatching AZ between node and PV is the #1 cause of Pending pods in multi-zone clusters.$escape$,
  $escape$apiVersion: storage.k8s.io/v1
kind: StorageClass
metadata:
  name: ebs-retain
provisioner: ebs.csi.aws.com
volumeBindingMode: WaitForFirstConsumer
reclaimPolicy: Retain
parameters:
  type: gp3
---
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: StatefulSet
metadata:
  name: postgres
spec:
  replicas: 2
  serviceName: postgres
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: postgres
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: postgres
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: postgres
        image: postgres:16
        volumeMounts:
        - name: data
          mountPath: /var/lib/postgresql/data
  volumeClaimTemplates:
  - metadata:
      name: data
    spec:
      accessModes: ["ReadWriteOnce"]
      storageClassName: ebs-retain
      resources:
        requests:
          storage: 20Gi$escape$,
  $escape$bash$escape$,
